No It Exp Sheet Instructions 10

1.Create Worksheet  No IT Exp

 

2.Add _cc.GenderMale>Female to colors

 

3. Add IT Exp to Rows




 

     

4.Add _cc.IT Exp% to Details

 

5.  RightClick and Hide Null



 

 

6.  Add  _cc.CountEntireTable to Columns.

 

7.  Hide the Color Legend


 


8.  Right Click IT Exp in Rows. Select Sort. Sort By Field Descending on _cc.CountEntireTable



9.  Double Click title. Replace Missing Field with <AGG(_cc.IT Exp%)>  .

 

10. Replace Black with No IT Exp

 


 

11.  Make sure the Format is the same as the Ethnicity Worksheet.


12. <AGG(_cc.IT Exp%)>  =t Tableau Bold , Font 24 , Bold and Grey black(#333333)


13. No IT Exp  = Tableau Book, Font 18, Bold and Pink(#fe019a).  Click OK Button.

 

14.  Right Click in the Work Sheet and Select FORMAT


15.  Click on the LINES icon. 

 

16.  Select NONE for Grid Lines, Axis Rulers\




17.  Click on the BORDERS Icon




18. Select NONE for Row Divider and Column Divider. Click on X to close.


19. Drag SUM([_cc_Gender=Male]) and SUM([_cc_Gender=FeMale]) to ToolTip


20.  Clean it up sot it only has 
       Male: <SUM(_cc_Gender=Male)>
       Female: <SUM(_cc_Gender=Female)>
